<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Irene B. Rosenfeld</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman of the Board and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chief Executive Officer</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Three Parkway North</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">April&nbsp;1, 2014 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dear Fellow Shareholders: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">I&#146;m pleased to invite you to our 2014 Annual Meeting of Shareholders that will be held at 9 a.m. CDT on Wednesday, May&nbsp;21, 2014, at the North Shore Center for
the Performing Arts in Skokie, Ill. During this meeting, we will review our 2013 performance and discuss our plans to continue delivering value to you, our shareholders. The center will open to shareholders at 8 a.m. If you wish to attend the
meeting, we ask that you register in advance by following the instructions included in the Proxy Statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have prepared the following materials for your
review prior the meeting: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Notice of Annual Meeting of Shareholders </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Proxy Statement describing the proposals to be voted on at the Annual Meeting </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Highlights of our 2013 financial and business performance </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As in the past, we&#146;re mailing a Notice of Internet
Availability of Proxy Materials with instructions on how to access these materials and vote online. Electronic delivery expedites the receipt of materials, lowers costs and reduces the environmental impact of our Annual Meeting. However, please
note, if you receive a Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials by mail, you won&#146;t receive paper copies of these materials unless you specifically request them by following the instructions on the Notice. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Your vote is important, and I encourage you to vote promptly. The Notice contains instructions on how to vote via the Internet or by calling a toll-free number. If you
receive paper copies of the proxy materials, you may also vote by signing, dating and mailing your proxy card or voting instruction form. You may also vote in person at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Highlights of Our 2013 Financial and Business Performance: </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Solid Results in a Challenging Environment </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">2013 was our first
full year as a global snacking company, and we delivered solid performance in a difficult macroeconomic environment. Specifically: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our market shares continued to grow, with about 70 percent of our revenues gaining or holding share </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reported net revenues increased 0.8 percent, and Organic Net Revenues<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> grew 3.9 percent, driven by the strongest volume/mix in our industry </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">In emerging markets, we grew at more than twice the company rate, with Brazil, Russia and India all up double-digits </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Power Brands &#150; our largest, fastest-growing and highest-margin brands that account for nearly 60 percent of our revenue<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP> &#150; increased 6.5 percent
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">On the bottom line, diluted earnings per share increased 28.1 percent, and Adjusted EPS<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> (previously referred to as Operating EPS) increased 13.5 percent on a
constant currency basis </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We generated strong Free Cash Flow excluding items<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</SUP> of nearly $2.3 billion </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">More than ever, we believe our competitive advantages set us apart and position us well to deliver top-tier financial
performance and create significant value for our shareholders: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Three-quarters of our revenue is derived from fast-growing snacks<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We are a market leader in all of our categories </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We have an unrivaled portfolio of iconic brands, proven innovation platforms and strong route-to-market capabilities </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We have an enviable geographic footprint, with nearly 40 percent of our revenue in fast-growing emerging markets<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</SUP> </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The plans we&#146;re executing now will enable us to deliver strong top-line growth, significantly expand margins, grow Adjusted EPS double digits and continue to
generate solid cash flow over the long term. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Targeting Best-in-Class Cost Management to Expand Margins </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Margin expansion remains a key priority. We continue to target operating income margins that are at or above peer levels. In particular, we see opportunities to drive
margin gains in developed markets. We&#146;re targeting operating income margin improvement of 500 and 250 basis points in North America and Europe, respectively, by 2016. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The biggest driver of margin gains will be the reinvention of our supply chain. Over the next three years, we expect to deliver $3 billion in gross productivity
savings, $1.5 billion in net productivity and $1 billion in incremental cash. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We&#146;ve already made significant progress on this initiative. Last year, we: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Upgraded over a third of our key supply chain leadership roles by recruiting and promoting our top talent </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Developed new global manufacturing platform for biscuits, chocolate and gum &#150; our Lines of the Future </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Redesigned our network by closing, selling or streamlining 30 plants. At the same time, we broke ground on leading-edge facilities in Mexico and India and announced significant expansions to facilities in the Czech
Republic, the UK and the U.S. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Achieved record gross productivity of 4.5 percent of costs of goods sold, while net productivity was a record 2.5 percent, double 2011 levels </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Reduced our cash conversion cycle by 50 percent </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition to our supply chain initiatives, we&#146;re also cutting
overhead costs, simplifying and standardizing processes, and implementing a zero-based budgeting discipline, as we create a more streamlined, more agile and more cost-conscious culture. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>The Call for Well-being </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe our financial well-being
also depends on protecting the well-being of our planet. That&#146;s why we&#146;ve made this one of five strategies to fuel our growth. As part of this strategy, we recently unveiled our Call for Well-being, a holistic approach to improve the
well-being of the planet and its people &#150; from farmers to consumers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Call for Well-being focuses on four action areas, each with clearly defined goals to
make a positive impact on our business and society. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Empowering consumers to snack mindfully.</B> We are focused on improving the nutrition of our current portfolio. Our goal is to reduce sodium and saturated fat by 10 percent and increase whole grains by 25 percent by
2020. We&#146;re also transforming our portfolio through new product innovation. We will grow our Better Choice products to 25 percent of our revenue by 2020 and increase our individually wrapped offerings of 200 calories or less by 25 percent. In
addition, we will help consumers make informed choices by providing calorie counts on the front of packaging globally by 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:14pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Based on 2013 net revenues of $35 billion. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Securing sustainable agricultural supplies of key commodities and reducing our environmental footprint</B><B>.</B> We&#146;re helping farmers create thriving communities with a 10-year, $600 million investment in our
Cocoa Life and Coffee Made Happy signature programs. We&#146;re also promoting biodiversity and good environmental practices through Harmony, our successful European wheat-sourcing program. By 2015, we will cut our energy, waste and water use by 15
percent, eliminate 50&nbsp;million pounds of packaging and have 60 percent of our production from zero waste to landfill sites. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Keeping consumers and our employees safe.</B> By 2015, all of our manufacturing facilities will achieve third-party food safety certification. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Investing in communities. </B>Over the next several years, we&#146;re investing $50 million in community partnerships to promote healthy lifestyle programs, focused on nutrition education and promoting active
lifestyles. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We recognize we don&#146;t have all the answers to these global societal challenges. But through our Call for Well-being, we believe we
can make a difference by using our global reach to partner with experts to bring together innovative ideas and help execute them at the local level. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Well-Positioned for Sustainable Growth </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Despite making
significant strides in our first year as a standalone company, we know we did not fully meet your or our expectations. We&#146;re committed to improving results in 2014 and beyond. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As the global macro-economy recovers, we expect growth rates for snacks to improve. And our margin improvement will help backstop that growth and ensure that we can
continue to deliver strong returns to shareholders. By leveraging our unique assets and executing our plans, I&#146;m confident that we will significantly expand margins and deliver strong top-line growth. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On behalf of all of our Mondel&#275;z International colleagues, I thank you for your continued support of our company as we deliver top-tier financial growth and build
a great place to work. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Best regards, </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g613688g23a97.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Irene B. Rosenfeld </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman and Chief Executive
Officer </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">

 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Forward-Looking Statements </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This letter to shareholders contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words, such as &#147;will,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148;
&#147;believe&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements. Examples of forward-looking statements include, but are not limited to, statements we make about our future performance, including future revenue
growth, earnings per share, margins and cash flow; the drivers of our future performance, including productivity improvements; category growth; shareholder returns; and our well-being initiatives. These forward-looking statements are subject to a
number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated in our forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, risks from
operating globally and in emerging markets, continued consumer weakness, continued volatility of commodity and other input costs, pricing actions, continued weakness in economic conditions, business disruptions, increased competition and tax law
changes. For additional information on these and other factors that could affect our forward-looking statements, see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in our filings with the U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K. We disclaim and do not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this letter to shareholders, except as required by applicable law or
regulation. </P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To approve the Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. Amended and Restated 2005 Performance Incentive Plan; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="38%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To ratify the selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as our independent registered public accountants for the fiscal year ending December&nbsp;31, 2014; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="38%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To vote on one shareholder proposal if properly presented at the meeting; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="38%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(6)</TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc613688_1"></A>Proxy Statement Summary </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>In this Proxy Statement Summary and throughout the Proxy Statement, &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; &#147;our,&#148; &#147;the Company,&#148; and &#147;Mondel&#275;z
International,&#148; refer to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>This Summary highlights select information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. You
should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully before voting and consider all information in the Proxy Statement. For more complete information regarding the Company&#146;s 2013 performance, please see our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year
ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Annual Meeting of Shareholders </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Voting at the 2014 Annual Meeting of Shareholders (Page 93) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All shareholders of record as of March&nbsp;14, 2014 may vote in person at the meeting. Beneficial owners may vote in person at the meeting if they have a legal proxy,
as described in the response to Question 14 on page 93. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Attending the Annual Meeting &#150; Important Note About Admission Requirements (Page 95)
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If you plan to attend the meeting in person, see the answer to Question 23 on page 95 for important details on admission requirements. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Frequently Asked Questions (Page 90) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We provide answers to
many frequently asked questions about the meeting and voting, including how to vote shares held in brokerage accounts and employee benefit plans, in the Q&amp;A section beginning on page 90 of this Proxy Statement. </P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px;MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;WIDTH:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Shareholder Engagement </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We regularly meet with and seek feedback from our shareholders on a wide range of matters. During 2013, we intensified our efforts to engage our largest shareholders
for two primary reasons. First, in the fall of 2013, as we completed our first year as Mondel&#275;z International, the Board and management wanted to better understand our shareholders&#146; perspectives on our progress, strategic outlook,
governance and other topics of interest to our shareholders. Second, while many of our shareholders voted to support our Say on Pay proposal at our 2013 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, the 78% favorable vote received was lower than votes in prior
years, and we wanted to better understand shareholder perspectives on our compensation programs and practices. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2013, our directors and senior management met
with over 40 of our largest shareholders. We very much appreciate the time that our shareholders devoted to preparing for and participating in these meetings and their willingness to share their points of view and suggestions. These meetings were
candid and constructive, and we will continue to solicit and consider our shareholders&#146; perspectives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See the Compensation Discussion and Analysis (page 34)
for a discussion of our shareholder outreach regarding our compensation practices. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;2. Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation
(Page 75) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Goals </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Human Resources and Compensation
Committee has identified four primary goals for our executive compensation program: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Attract, retain and motivate talented executive officers and develop world-class business leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Support business strategies that promote superior long-term shareholder returns; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our Named Executive Officers&#146; compensation dependent on achieving financial and other critical strategic and individual goals; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align our Named Executive Officers&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests through stock ownership guidelines and equity-based incentive awards that link executive compensation to sustained and superior Total Shareholder
Return. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Design </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our executive
compensation program to achieve these goals by: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Linking pay to performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Putting pay at risk based on short term and long term performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Setting meaningful performance goals; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Requiring our executive officers to keep a significant portion of their compensation in Company shares. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Our
Executives&#146; 2013 Compensation Reflected Their and Our Performance </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Although our 2013 financial results were solid, they were below the goals we had set at the beginning of the year. As a result, the awards earned by our Named Executive Officers under our Annual Cash Incentive Program
were generally below target. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Total Shareholder Return<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP>&nbsp;exceeded that of our peers over the past one- and three-year periods. Because the three-year performance cycle for our Long-Term
Incentive Plan incents performance based in part on Total Shareholder Return, our Named Executive Officers&#146; Long-Term Incentive Plan awards for the 2011-2013 performance cycle exceeded target. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Total Shareholder Return reflects share price performance including dividends paid for the one- and three-year periods ending December&nbsp;31, 2013. </TD></TR></TABLE>

shareholders and to motivate our executives to achieve both short- and long-term performance to drive top-tier Total Shareholder Return. To enable future awards, we are asking shareholders to approve amendments to the Mondel&#275;z International,
Inc. Amended and Restated 2005 Performance Incentive Plan. The amendments would: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc613688_2"></A>ITEM 1. Election of Directors </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc613688_3"></A>Process for Nominating Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee of our Board of Directors (the &#147;Governance Committee&#148;) is responsible for identifying, evaluating and
recommending to the Board director nominees for election at the 2014 Annual Meeting of Shareholders (and any adjournments or postponements of the meeting) (the &#147;Annual Meeting&#148;). The Governance Committee invites director nominee
suggestions from the directors, shareholders, management and others. From time to time, the Governance Committee retains third-party executive search firms to assist in identifying and evaluating potential director nominees. Mr.&nbsp;Peltz, who is
standing for election by our shareholders for the first time, was recommended to the Board as a director nominee by a shareholder. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>General Qualifications
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes all directors should possess certain personal characteristics, including integrity, sound business judgment and vision, to serve on our
Board. We believe these characteristics are necessary to establish a competent, ethical and well-functioning Board that best represents the interests of our shareholders. Under our Corporate Governance Guidelines (the &#147;Guidelines&#148;), when
evaluating the suitability of individuals for nomination, the Governance Committee takes into account many factors. These include the individual&#146;s general understanding of the varied disciplines relevant to the success of a large,
publicly-traded company in today&#146;s global business environment, understanding of our global businesses and markets, professional expertise and educational background and other factors that promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience.
The Governance Committee also considers an individual&#146;s ability to devote sufficient time and effort to fulfill his or her Mondel&#275;z International responsibilities, taking into account the individual&#146;s other commitments. In addition,
the Governance Committee considers whether an individual meets various independence requirements, including whether his or her service on boards and committees of other organizations is consistent with our conflicts of interest policy. The
Governance Committee also evaluates each individual in the context of the Board as a whole, with the objective of recruiting and recommending a slate of director nominees that can best perpetuate the Company&#146;s success and represent shareholder
interests through the exercise of sound judgment and informed decision-making. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, under our Guidelines, the Governance Committee generally will not
recommend and the Board will not nominate an individual or re-nominate for election an independent director after he or she reaches age 75. However, the Governance Committee and Board may do so in extraordinary circumstances if nomination or
re-nomination is in the shareholders&#146; best interests because the candidate is uniquely qualified to contribute to a specific dimension of the Board&#146;s work and Company&#146;s growth in the subsequent year. If the Governance Committee
determines that the individual&#146;s nomination or re-nomination for election is in the shareholders&#146; best interests, the Governance Committee may recommend, and the Board may approve, that director&#146;s nomination or re-nomination for up to
three annual terms following his or her 75<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> birthday. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In considering whether to nominate Mr.&nbsp;Tata, age
76, for re-election by the Company&#146;s shareholders, both the Governance Committee and the Board reviewed Mr.&nbsp;Tata&#146;s unique experience and expertise in leading a successful global enterprise; knowledge of Indian, Asian and emerging
markets and cultural affairs; support for the development and promotion of innovative business practices; and insights into the continuing evolution of consumer products. Both the Governance Committee and the Board determined that Mr.&nbsp;Tata
would uniquely contribute to the Board&#146;s work and the Company&#146;s growth during the coming year. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">A management director must resign from the Board upon
ceasing to be a Company officer. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Diversity </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As noted above, the
Guidelines provide that the Governance Committee will consider factors that promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience when evaluating the suitability of individuals for nomination. While the Board has no formal written policy regarding
what specific factors would create such diversity, the Governance Committee </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">recognizes the significant benefit diversity provides to the Board and Mondel&#275;z International, as varying viewpoints
contribute to a more informed and effective decision-making process. The Governance Committee seeks broad experience in relevant industries, professions and areas of expertise important to our operations, including global business, manufacturing,
marketing, science, finance and accounting, academia, law and regulation. The Governance Committee also recognizes the importance of having directors with significant international experiences and backgrounds given our global, multicultural
business. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our director nominees have significant and relevant operating experience, global and diverse perspectives and financial expertise. Their varied
experiences, backgrounds and personal characteristics provide the Board with a diversity of viewpoints and enable it to represent effectively our shareholders: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">11 director nominees have operating and general management experience at major global companies, including consumer products companies; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">3 director nominees are women, including the Chairman; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">director nominees range in age from 52 to 76. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Six of our director nominees served as Company directors before the
Company spun off Kraft Foods Group, Inc. to shareholders on October&nbsp;1, 2012. Six of our director nominees joined the Board at or following October&nbsp;1, 2012. The resulting composition of the Board provides continuity as well as new expertise
and perspectives relevant to the Board&#146;s work. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual Experience, Qualifications, Attributes and Skills </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee works with the Board to determine the appropriate mix of characteristics, professional experience and areas of expertise that result in a Board
that is strong in its collective knowledge, allowing the Board to fulfill its responsibilities and best perpetuate our long-term success and represent all shareholders&#146; interests. When evaluating potential director nominees, the Governance
Committee considers each individual&#146;s professional expertise and educational background in addition to their general qualifications. The Governance Committee evaluates each individual in the context of the Board as a whole. To help the
Governance Committee determine whether director nominees qualify to serve on our Board and would contribute to the Board&#146;s current and future needs, director nominees complete questionnaires regarding their backgrounds, qualifications, skills
and potential conflicts of interest. Additionally, the Governance Committee annually conducts evaluations of the Board and the Board&#146;s committees, and coordinates individual directors&#146; self-assessments that assess the experience,
qualifications, attributes, skills, diversity and contributions of each individual and of the Board as a whole. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee regularly communicates
with the Board to identify characteristics, professional experience and areas of expertise that are particularly desirable for our directors to possess to meet specific Board needs, including: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><A NAME="toc613688_4"></A>Shareholder Nominee Recommendations </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Governance Committee will consider any candidate whom a shareholder recommends for election to the Board. The shareholder should submit to the Corporate Secretary the recommended candidate and the same information set forth in the By-Laws as
required for a shareholder to nominate a candidate for election to the Board at an Annual Meeting. The Governance Committee uses the same criteria set forth in the Guidelines to evaluate a candidate recommended by a shareholder as the Governance
Committee uses to evaluate a candidate it identifies, as described above under &#147;Item 1. Election of Directors &#150; Process for Nominating Directors.&#148; It then makes a recommendation to the Board regarding the candidate&#146;s appointment
or nomination for election to the Board. After the Board&#146;s consideration of the candidate recommended by a shareholder, our Corporate Secretary notifies that shareholder whether the Board decided to appoint or nominate the candidate. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For a description of how shareholders may nominate a candidate for election to the Board at an annual meeting of shareholders and have that nomination included in the
proxy statement for that meeting, see &#147;2015 Annual Meeting of Shareholders&#148; in this Proxy Statement. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc613688_5"></A>Director
Nominees </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that all the director nominees for election at the Annual Meeting are highly qualified. Each director nominee&#146;s specific
experience, qualifications, attributes and skills that the Governance Committee relied upon when determining whether to nominate the individual for election are described below in the director nominee&#146;s biography. (A particular director nominee
may possess other skills, knowledge or experience in addition to those described below.) As their biographies indicate, all the director nominees have significant leadership history, professional experience, knowledge, including industry knowledge,
and skills that qualify them for service on our Board. They represent diverse views, experiences and backgrounds. Each director nominee other than the Chairman satisfies independence requirements under the NASDAQ listing standards and the
Board&#146;s categorical standards of director independence. All director nominees satisfy the criteria set forth in our Guidelines and possess the personal characteristics essential for the proper and effective functioning of the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Board currently has twelve directors, all of whom are standing for election at the 2014 Annual Meeting. Shareholders elected eleven of the directors to one-year
terms at the 2013 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. The Board appointed one additional director, Mr.&nbsp;Nelson Peltz, on January&nbsp;21, 2014. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All directors are
elected annually. The Governance Committee recommended, and the Board nominated, each of the 12 director nominees listed below for election at the Annual Meeting. The terms of all directors elected at the 2014 Annual Meeting will end at the 2015
Annual Meeting of Shareholders or when a director&#146;s successor has been duly elected and qualified. Each director nominee has consented to his or her nomination for election to the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following information regarding each director nominee is as of February&nbsp;28, 2014, including information about each director nominee&#146;s professional
experience, educational background, attributes and qualifications that led the </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8 </FONT></P>

U.S. publicly-listed company directorships listed below, the director nominees may also serve on the boards of various private and non-U.S. companies and charitable, educational and cultural institutions, not all of which are included in their
biographies. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The persons named as proxies on each shareholder&#146;s proxy card will vote the shares represented by the proxy card FOR or AGAINST the director
nominees or ABSTAIN from voting, as indicated in the shareholder&#146;s voting instructions. If a director nominee should become unavailable to serve as a director, the persons named as proxies intend to vote the shares for a replacement director
nominee designated by the Board. In lieu of naming a substitute, the Board may reduce the number of directors on our Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>THE BOARD RECOMMENDS SHAREHOLDERS

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>LEWIS W.K. BOOTH</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, Ford Motor Company</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since October 2012</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committees:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Audit</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 65</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Booth served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of the Ford Motor Company, a global
automobile manufacturer, from November 2008 until his retirement in April 2012. He was Executive Vice President, Ford of Europe, Volvo Car Corporation and Ford Export Operations and Global Growth Initiatives, and Executive Vice President of
Ford&#146;s Premier Automotive Group, from October 2005 to October 2008. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Booth held various executive leadership positions with Ford, including as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Ford of Europe, President of Mazda
Motor Corporation and President of Ford Asia Pacific and Africa Operations. He was employed continuously by the Ford Motor Company, in positions of increasing responsibility, from 1978 to 2012.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Booth is a qualified chartered management accountant.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Booth was appointed Commander of the Order of the British Empire in the Queen&#146;s Birthday
Honours list in June&nbsp;2012, for his services to the United Kingdom&#146;s automotive and manufacturing industries.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Booth received a Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering
with honors from the University of Liverpool.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Boards:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Booth is a director of Gentherm Incorporated and Rolls-Royce Holdings&nbsp;plc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>LOIS D. JULIBER</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Vice Chairman and<BR>Chief Operating Officer,
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Colgate-Palmolive</FONT> Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since November
2007</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committees:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Governance, Membership and Public Affairs</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chair, Human Resources and Compensation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 65</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms. Juliber served as Vice Chairman of the Colgate-Palmolive Company, a global consumer products company, from
October 2004 until her retirement in April 2005. She served as Colgate-Palmolive&#146;s Chief Operating Officer from February 2000 to October 2004, Executive Vice President &#150; North America and Europe from 1997 until February&nbsp;2000 and
President of Colgate North America from 1994 to 1997. Prior to joining Colgate-Palmolive, Ms.&nbsp;Juliber spent 15 years at Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s predecessor, General Foods Corporation, in a variety of key marketing and general
management positions.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms. Juliber received a Bachelor of Arts from Wellesley College and a<BR>Master of Business Administration from Harvard University.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Boards:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms. Juliber is a director of E. I. du Pont de Nemours and Company. She was formerly a director of Goldman Sachs Group, Inc.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership and Operating experience &#150; former Vice Chairman
and Chief Operating Officer of a global consumer products company, where she led the company&#146;s expansion into a number of key emerging markets, including China;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Industry Knowledge, Product Development and Marketing, and
Global Business experience &#150; 32 years working in the global consumer products industry; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance experience &#150;
current and former director of other global public companies.</P></TD></TR>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>MARK D. KETCHUM</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former President and<BR>Chief Executive Officer,<BR>Newell Rubbermaid Inc.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since April 2007</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Lead Director since January 2009</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 64</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Ketchum served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Newell Rubbermaid Inc., a global marketer of
consumer and commercial products, from October 2005 to June 2011 and was a member of its board of directors from November 2004 to May 2012. From 1971 to 2004, Mr. Ketchum served in a variety of roles of increasing responsibility at The Procter &amp;
Gamble Company, a global marketer of consumer products, including President, Global Baby and Family Care, from 1999 to 2004, President &#150; North American Paper Sector from 1996 to 1999, and Vice President and General Manager &#150; Tissue/Towel
from 1990 to 1996.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Ketchum received a Bachelor of Science in Industrial Engineering and Operations Research from Cornell University.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Board:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Ketchum was formerly a director of Newell Rubbermaid Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership and Operating experience &#150; former President and Chief Executive Officer of a global consumer products company and former President of a division of another global consumer
products company;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Industry Knowledge, Product Development
and Marketing and Global Business experience &#150; held key roles in operations, marketing and general management at global consumer products companies for four decades; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance experience &#150;
former director of other global public companies.</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since January 2014</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committees:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Governance, Membership and Public Affairs</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 71</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Peltz has served as Chief Executive Officer and Founding Partner of Trian Fund Management, L.P., an
alternative investment management firm, since November 2005.&nbsp;He also served as Chairman and CEO of Triarc Companies, Inc. (now known as The Wendy&#146;s Company), a holding company for various consumer and industrial businesses, from April 1993
to June 2007, and has served as its non-executive Chairman since June 2007. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Peltz served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Trian Group, Limited Partnership, which provided investment banking and management services
to entities controlled by Mr. Peltz and Peter May,&nbsp;from January 1989 to April 1993 and as Chairman and CEO of Triangle Industries, Inc., a manufacturer of packaging products, from 1983 to December 1988.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2012, Mr. Peltz was recognized for a third consecutive year by the National Association of
Corporate Directors as among the most influential persons in the global corporate governance arena.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Pennsylvania.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Boards:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Peltz is a director of The Wendy&#146;s Company, Legg Mason, Inc. and Ingersoll-Rand plc.&nbsp;He was formerly a director of H. J. Heinz Company.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>

Chief Executive Officer of an investment management firm, former Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of a consumer/industrial holding company and a global manufacturing company; and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate Governance experience &#150;
current and former director of other global public companies and recognition as an influential person in the global corporate governance arena.</P></TD></TR>

<IMG SRC="g613688reynolds.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>FREDRIC G. REYNOLDS</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Former Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, CBS&nbsp;Corporation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since December 2007</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committees:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Chair, Audit</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 63</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Reynolds served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of CBS Corporation, a mass media
company, from January 2006 until his retirement in August 2009. From September 2001 until December 2005, Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Viacom Television Stations Group and as Executive Vice President and Chief
Financial Officer of Viacom Inc., a mass media company, from May 2000 to September 2001. He also served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of CBS Corporation and its predecessor, Westinghouse Electric Corporation, from 1994 to
2000. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds served in various capacities at PepsiCo, Inc., a food and beverage company, for twelve years, including Chief Financial Officer or Financial Officer at Pizza Hut, Pepsi Cola International, Kentucky Fried
Chicken Worldwide and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Frito-Lay.</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Reynolds is a
certified public accountant.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Reynolds received a Bachelor of Business Administration in Finance from the University of Miami.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Boards:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Reynolds is a director of AOL, Inc. and Hess Corporation.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>RATAN N. TATA</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman,</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Tata
Trusts</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since May 2013</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committees:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Governance, Membership and Public Affairs</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Human Resources and Compensation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Age: 76</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Tata is Chairman of the Tata Trusts, among the largest private sector philanthropic trusts in India.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Tata previously served as Chairman of Tata Sons Limited, the holding company of the Tata Group,
one of India&#146;s largest business conglomerates, from 1991 until December&nbsp;2012. Mr. Tata was also Chairman of the major Tata Group companies, including Tata Motors, Tata Steel, Tata Consultancy Services, Tata Global Beverages and several
other Tata companies, until December&nbsp;2012. Mr. Tata joined the Tata Group in December 1962. Under Mr. Tata&#146;s leadership, the Tata Group acquired several global businesses, including Tetley, Corus and Jaguar Land Rover, and grew from an
India-centric company into a global enterprise. Mr. Tata&#146;s extensive business experience includes his tenure as a former director of Bombay Dyeing and Manufacturing Company Ltd. and as a current member of international advisory boards of
Mitsubishi Corp., JPMorgan Chase, Rolls-Royce, Temasek Holdings and Monetary Authority of Singapore. Mr. Tata also serves on the United Kingdom Prime Minister&#146;s Business Counsel for Britain.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Tata received a Bachelor of Architecture from Cornell University and completed the Advanced Management Program at Harvard Business School.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Boards:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. Tata is a director of Alcoa Inc. and was formerly a director of Fiat S.p.A.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership and Operating experience &#150; former Chairman of the holding company for one of India&#146;s largest business conglomerates, with revenues in excess of $100 billion, and former
Chairman of major operating companies in various industries, including automotive, beverages, consulting and steel;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Global Business experience &#150; former Chairman of the holding company for one of India&#146;s largest business conglomerates and former Chairman of multiple companies with international
operations, service on numerous international advisory boards, and a proven track record growing global brands, notably in emerging markets;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Industry Knowledge and Marketing experience &#150; former Chairman of
a global beverage company; and</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Public Company Board and Corporate
Governance experience &#150; current and former director of other global public companies.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>JEAN-FRAN&Ccedil;OIS M. L. VAN&nbsp;BOXMEER</B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman of the Executive Board and Chief Executive Officer, Heineken N.V.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since January 2010</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Current Committees:</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Human Resources And Compensation</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr. van Boxmeer has been Chairman of the Executive Board and Chief Executive Officer of Heineken N.V., a global
brewing company, since 2005 and a member of its Executive Board since 2001. He has been employed continuously by Heineken, in various capacities, in positions of increasing responsibility, since 1984.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Education:</I></P>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Public Company Board:</I></P>

 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Leadership and Operating experience &#150; Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of a global brewing company, where he led the company&#146;s significant global expansion, most notably in
