<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Cash Compensation &#150; Board, Lead Director and Committee Chair Retainers </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We pay our non-employee directors their cash retainers quarterly. Pursuant to the Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. 2001 Compensation Plan for Non-Employee Directors,
they can defer 25%, 50%, 75% or 100% of their cash retainers into notional unfunded accounts that mirror certain of the investment options under the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Thrift 401(k) Plan. If the Board appoints a non-employee director during
the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of shareholders), we pay that director a prorated retainer based on the number of days remaining in the calendar year. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Equity Compensation &#150; Annual Stock Awards </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Annual stock awards are made
following the annual meeting of shareholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If the Board appoints a non-employee director during the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of
shareholders), the director receives a prorated stock award upon appointment. We calculate the value of prorated award using this ratio: the number of months until the next annual meeting of shareholders over a denominator of twelve months. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Non-employee director annual stock awards are made in the form of vested deferred stock. Distribution of actual shares is deferred until six&nbsp;months after the
director ends his or her service as a director. When dividends are paid on the Company&#146;s common shares, we accrue the value of the dividends that would have been paid on the deferred stock. Six months after the director ends his or her service
as a director, we issue shares to the director equal to the accrued value. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Equity Holding Requirement </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To align further the interests of our non-employee directors with our shareholders, we require our non-employee directors to hold shares of our common stock in an amount
equal to five times the annual Board retainer (i.e, $550,000) within five years of becoming a director. If a non-employee director does not meet the stock ownership requirement within that timeframe, the Lead Director will consider the non-employee
director&#146;s particular situation and may take action as he deems appropriate. As of February&nbsp;28, 2014 each director who has served for at least five years met or exceeded this requirement. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z
INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;32 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Company Match for Director Charitable Contributions </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Non-employee directors are eligible to participate in the Mondel&#275;z International Foundation Matching Gift Program on the same terms as our U.S. employees. Each
year, the Foundation will match up to $15,000 in contributions by a non-employee director to a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization(s). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2013 Non-Employee Director
Compensation Table </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc613688_31"></A>Compensation Discussion and Analysis </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc613688_32"></A>Executive Summary </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This executive
summary: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Highlights how we performed for the one- and three-year periods ending December&nbsp;31, 2013, and shows how our NEOs&#146; pay correlated with our performance, </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Explains how we responded to our shareholders&#146; 2013 Say on Pay advisory vote, and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Illustrates how our compensation design principles and governance practices protect and promote our shareholders&#146; interests. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The remainder of this Compensation Discussion and Analysis: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Highlights how our compensation design objectives and governance principles align our compensation practices with our shareholders&#146; interests; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Explains the Compensation Committee&#146;s rationale for our NEOs&#146; 2013 compensation, and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Illustrates how our NEOs&#146; 2013 compensation correlates with their, and our, 2013 performance. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our NEOs for 2013
were: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="26%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Our Goal is to Align Pay with Performance </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee remains committed to pay-for-performance. We design our executive compensation to incent our NEOs to deliver exceptional short- and long-term
results with a strong emphasis on long-term incentives. The Compensation Committee believes that its decisions relating to our NEOs&#146; 2013 compensation demonstrate this alignment between pay and performance. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2013 Performance Highlights </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2013, our first full year as a global snacks
company: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our reported net revenues increased 0.8%, and our Organic Net Revenues<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> increased 3.9% driven primarily by strong volume/mix. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We delivered strong market share performance, with nearly 70% of revenues gaining or holding share, in the face of a significant slowdown in our categories as the year progressed. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our diluted earnings per share increased 28.1% and our Adjusted Earnings Per Share<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> (previously referred to as Operating Earnings Per Share) increased 13.5% on a
constant currency basis. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We generated Free Cash Flow excluding items<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> of nearly $2.3 billion. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We returned $3.6 billion to our shareholders in the form of share repurchases and dividends. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2013 Performance and Impact on Annual Cash Incentive Program Awards </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Despite solid growth in 2013, we did not reach two of the three performance targets established under our 2013 Annual Cash Incentive Program. This resulted in a
corporate rating of 77% of target under the program. Consequently, the awards earned by our NEOs in 2013 under our Annual Cash Incentive Program were generally below target. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2011-2013 Performance and Impact on LTIP Award </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our TSR<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> exceeded our peers&#146; TSR over the past one- and three-year periods. Because the three-year
performance cycle for our Long-Term Incentive Plan (&#147;LTIP&#148;) incents performance based in part on TSR, our NEOs&#146; LTIP awards for the 2011-2013 performance cycle exceeded target. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>TSR Results for Mondel&#275;z International<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The LTIP award for the 2011-2013 performance cycle ended on December&nbsp;31, 2013, was based on a weighted average
performance rating that included our performance during the period January&nbsp;1, 2011-September&nbsp;30, 2012 prior to the Spin-Off (the &#147;Pre Spin-Off&#148; period) and our performance during the period October&nbsp;1, 2012-December&nbsp;31,
2013 following the Spin-Off (the &#147;Post Spin-Off&#148; period). Overall, our results were above target for the 2011-2013 performance cycle. Over the performance cycle, we achieved solid Organic Net Revenue Growth, solid Adjusted Earnings Per
Share Growth (as defined under &#147;&#150; Elements of Executive Compensation &#150; Long-Term Incentives &#150; 2013-2015 LTIP Performance Cycle&#148;) and strong share price performance including dividends paid in comparison to our Performance
Peer Group during the performance cycle (&#147;Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return&#148;). During this period, our Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return was above the 90th percentile of both our Pre Spin-Off and Post Spin-Off
Performance Peer Groups, significantly surpassing the Performance Peer Group&#146;s median. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following chart reflects our actual performance against targets for
the LTIP&#146;s 2011-2013 Pre Spin-Off and Post Spin-Off performance cycles: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><B>Adjusted Earnings Per Share Growth</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Above 93<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">rd</SUP><BR>Percentile<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Median</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Above 90<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP><BR>Percentile<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP></TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return was 20.7% compared to our Pre Spin-Off Performance Peer Group&#146;s median of 10.1%. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Annualized Relative Total Shareholder Return was 23.2% compared to our Post Spin-Off Performance Peer Group&#146;s median of 17.2%. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based on these results, the LTIP rating for the 2011-2013 performance cycle was 148% of target. See &#147; &#150; Elements of Executive Compensation &#150; Long-Term
Incentives&#148; for more information about our LTIP. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Our Chief Executive Officer&#146;s 2013 Total Compensation Decreased From 2012 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Reflecting our Compensation Committee&#146;s objective of aligning pay with performance, when excluding Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld&#146;s one-time special equity award and
increase in pension value in 2012, Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld&#146;s compensation decreased slightly in 2013 due primarily to a lower award under our 2013 Annual Cash Incentive Program. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld&#146;s 2013 total compensation as reported in the Summary Compensation Table decreased sharply from 2012 primarily due to the absence of the 2012
one-time special equity grant and no increase in the value of her pension. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>How the Compensation Committee Considered the Shareholder Advisory Vote on our 2012
Executive Compensation Program </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We received a 78% level of support in 2013 for our shareholder advisory vote on Say on Pay following a 96% level of support in
2012. Due to the decline in the level of support, both the Compensation Committee and management wanted to understand better our shareholders&#146; perspectives on our compensation programs and practices. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Following the filing of our 2013 proxy statement and prior to the 2013 Annual Meeting, we discussed with many of our largest shareholders their views on the matters in
that proxy statement, including executive compensation. Following our 2013 Annual Meeting, we met with more than 40 of our largest shareholders representing over 40% of our outstanding shares, as well as proxy advisors. In varying combinations, our
non-employee directors and members of senior management participated in those meetings. The Compensation Committee also obtained additional analysis from both CAP, the Compensation Committee&#146;s independent compensation consultant, and from
MacKenzie Partners, a proxy solicitation firm. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In general, we believe our shareholders support our overall compensation philosophy, programs and practices. They
provided varying perspectives on specific decisions and aspects of our programs. Based on the feedback we received, we believe that the lower support level was due to the one-time equity grants made in late 2012 to three NEOs. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;36 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The results of the 2013 Say on Pay vote and feedback from the discussions with shareholders formed the basis of the
Compensation Committee&#146;s refinements to the program design for 2014. Taking into account shareholder input, the Compensation Committee is changing two performance standards in our 2014 incentive programs to better align them with our strategies
and objectives as follows. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>2014 Annual Cash Incentive Program:</I> adding a metric measuring market share performance in our key markets and categories. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;background-color:#eaeaea;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Compensation Design Principles and Governance Practices </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We
intend our executive compensation design and our compensation governance practices to protect and promote our shareholders&#146; interests. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Design Principles. </I></B> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>What we do:</I></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><I>What we don&#146;t do:</I></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Link pay to performance</U>. We reward our NEOs</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">based upon the value they add.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Put pay at risk based on performance</U>. Almost</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">85% of our CEO&#146;s pay and over 70% of our other</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">NEOs&#146; pay is at-risk. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Target pay at the median of our peer group</U>. We</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">compensate fairly and competitively, but not</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">excessively.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Set meaningful performance goals at the</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>beginning of the performance period</U>.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Intend to qualify performance based compensation</U></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>under Section 162(m)</U>.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Incent short-term results to the detriment of long-</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>term goals</U>.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Incent excessively risky business strategies</U>.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Governance Practices.</I></B> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>What we do:</I></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><I>What we don&#146;t do:</I></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD HEIGHT="8"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Require significant stock ownership</U>. Our </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">requirements are comparable to, or more</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">stringent than, our Compensation Survey Group&#146;s</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">median.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Require executives to retain equity compensation</U>.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We require our NEOs to hold for one year all net</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">shares awarded and all net shares acquired upon</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">the exercise of stock options.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Provide for &#147;clawbacks.&#148;</U> We can recoup incentive</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">compensation in the event of certain financial</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">restatements.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Prohibit hedging, pledging or short sales</U>.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>The Compensation Committee retains an</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>independent compensation consultant</U>. The</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">consultant does no work for the Company other</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">than advising the Compensation Committee.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="2">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Provide NEOs with tax gross ups for perquisites</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>or upon a change in control</U>. Taxes are our</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">NEOs&#146; responsibility.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Re-price underwater stock options</U>. We do not re-</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">price outstanding stock options, whether vested</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">or unvested.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Pay dividends on unvested or unearned</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>performance shares</U>. We do not pay accrued</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">dividend equivalents unless and until the</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">applicable performance targets are met and we</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">deliver the shares awarded.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Enter into employment agreements with our</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>NEOs</U>. We do not give our NEOs employment</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">contracts. We do not guarantee salary increases</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">or bonus amounts.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#120;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Provide separate benefit plans for our NEOs</U>.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our NEOs participate in the same benefit plans</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:3.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">available to salaried U.S. employees.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Perform an annual compensation risk assessment</U>.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Engage shareholders</U>. See the discussion above.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>Limit perquisites</U>. We provide types of</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">perquisites comparable to those provided by</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">companies in our Compensation Survey Group.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#254;</FONT></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;<U>In the event of a change in control, pay severance</U></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><U>and vest equity only upon a double trigger</U>. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#147;Double trigger&#148; requires both a change in</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">control and termination of the executive&#146;s</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:4.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">employment without cause or for good reason.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> </div>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;38 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc613688_33"></A>Our Compensation Program Design </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee has identified four primary goals for our executive compensation programs: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">attract, retain and motivate talented executive officers and develop world-class business leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">support business strategies that promote superior long-term shareholder returns; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our NEOs&#146; compensation dependent on achieving financial and other critical strategic and individual goals; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">align our NEOs&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests through stock ownership guidelines and equity-based incentive awards that link executive compensation to sustained and superior TSR. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our executive compensation program to achieve these goals by using the following strategies: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Use Fixed and Variable Compensation.</I></B> We use a mix of fixed and variable compensation (heavily weighted to variable compensation for our NEOs) designed to
attract, retain and motivate top-performing executives, as well as to appropriately align compensation levels with achieving relevant financial and strategic goals. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Use Equity and Cash Incentives.</I></B> We use a mix of equity and cash incentives heavily weighted toward equity to focus NEOs on achieving long-term TSR that
exceeds that of our peers. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Compensate Based on Individual Performance.</I></B> We consider individual performance in making decisions for most elements of
compensation. We also consider an individual&#146;s potential for advancement within the organization in making equity grants (other than LTIP). </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Require NEOs
to be Significant Shareholders.</I></B> We require our NEOs to own specified levels of Mondel&#275;z International shares to align their interests with those of our shareholders. Our compensation programs facilitate attainment of high levels of
stock ownership. We also require that our NEOs hold for one year net shares (after taxes) received upon exercise of stock options, the removal of restrictions on restricted stock and the award of Company shares upon satisfaction of performance
conditions. See &#147;&#150; Elements of Executive Compensation &#150; Long-Term Incentives &#150; Requiring Stock Ownership&#148; for more information on stock ownership guidelines. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Benchmark Our Compensation Against Relevant Comparators.</I></B> Each year, we use two separate groups of companies to benchmark the compensation that we offer
our NEOs and the performance that impacts our NEOs&#146; compensation: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Compensation Survey Group; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our Performance Peer Group. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">With the input of CAP, the Compensation Committee reviews the composition of these
comparator groups annually to ensure that their composition remains appropriate. The Compensation Committee made no changes to either group for 2013, with the exception of the removal of H. J. Heinz Company from the Performance Peer Group because it
ceased to be a public company in 2013. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">There is substantial overlap (10 of the 12 companies) between our Performance Peer Group and our Compensation Survey Group.
Our Performance Peer Group differs from our Compensation Survey Group because the companies in our Performance Peer Group are primarily in the food and non-alcoholic beverage industry (9 of the 12 companies in the Performance Peer Group versus 8 of
the 21 companies in the Compensation Survey Group) and we include companies in our Performance Peer Group regardless of revenue size or market capitalization. See &#147;&#150; Composition and Purpose of our Compensation Survey Group&#148; and
&#147;&#150; Composition and Purpose of our Performance Peer Group&#148; below for additional information. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Pay competitively but not excessively.</I></B> We
benchmark to ensure that our executive compensation and benefits package is competitive with our Compensation Survey Group but not excessive. In addition, we compare our financial and TSR performance against our Performance Peer Group. The
Performance Peer Group comparison allows us to link long-term incentive compensation to the delivery of superior financial results relative to industry peers. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;39 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Composition and Purpose of our Compensation Survey Group </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each year, our Compensation Committee compares our compensation programs with those of our Compensation Survey Group companies to assess whether our compensation program
and our target compensation levels are consistent with market practice. In constructing our Compensation Survey Group, our Compensation Committee considers global, top-tier companies with the following attributes: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Similar revenue size </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Similar market capitalization </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Primarily focused on food/beverage or consumer/household products or are consumer-facing companies </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Executive positions similar in breadth, complexity and/or scope of responsibility </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

criteria: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:3.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">United Parcel Service, Inc.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-left:3.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Kellogg Company</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Competitive Positioning </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In determining
appropriate compensation levels for our NEOs, our Compensation Committee reviews compensation levels for similarly situated executives at companies in our Compensation Survey Group. Aon Hewitt (&#147;Aon&#148;) provides the compensation data. At the
request of the Compensation Committee, CAP reviews and evaluates Aon&#146;s data. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee&#146;s compensation strategy is to target total direct
compensation, including base salary and annual and long-term incentives, at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Group. Company performance and individual performance will determine whether actual pay received is above or below the
Compensation Survey Group median. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To further validate our compensation levels, our Compensation Committee evaluates the pay for performance alignment between our
Company and the Compensation Survey Group on a retroactive basis, using data provided by CAP. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;40 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Composition and Purpose of our Performance Peer Group </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our Compensation Committee uses our Performance Peer Group to help establish meaningful performance targets for our LTIP at the outset of a performance cycle. At the end
of the performance cycle, we evaluate our TSR relative to the median TSR of our Performance Peer Group to determine whether that LTIP performance measure has been reached or exceeded. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our 2013 Performance Peer Group<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> is comprised of companies primarily focused on the production and marketing of
food and non-alcoholic beverages. Because the companies in this group directly compete with us, comparing our performance with the group&#146;s median performance provides the best measure of our performance. This group is less relevant when we
compare compensation levels for certain executive positions because size and complexity factors reduce comparability. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Long-Term/Stock-Based Incentive Compensation</B></P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Plan (Performance</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Shares)</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Each NEO receives a grant of performance shares at the outset of a three-year performance cycle. Grants are based on a percentage of base salary. Actual awards
are determined at the end of the performance cycle by evaluating actual performance against corporate performance targets. Awards can be 0% to 200% of target, based on our performance. Awards are delivered in Mondel&#275;z International common
stock.</TD>

interests</P></TD></TR>

(&#147;NQSOs&#148;) vest 33% per year on the first two grant anniversary dates and 34% on the third anniversary date.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recognize advancement potential</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enhance stock ownership/align with shareholders&#146;

<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">Restricted Stock</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

stock vests three years after the grant date.</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Retain and attract talent</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Drive top-tier performance</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Long-term
individual contribution</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4.50em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#150;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Recognize advancement potential</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enhance stock ownership/align with shareholders&#146;
interests</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="font-size:1px; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:6pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Executive
Benefits</B></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Voluntary Non-Qualified</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Deferred Compensation</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Plan</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Program that allows U.S. executive officers to defer, on a pre-tax basis, certain defined compensation elements with flexible distribution options to meet
future financial goals.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

security</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">Generally limited to a car allowance, financial counseling and, for the CEO only, personal use of Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s aircraft.</TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc613688_34"></A>Elements of Executive Compensation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Base Salary </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Base salary is the principal fixed element of executive
compensation. In setting base salaries for NEOs, our Compensation Committee generally targets base salary to be at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Group based on the corresponding executive role. Our Compensation Committee also
considers a number of other factors when setting base salaries for NEOs, including: Company performance and the NEO&#146;s individual performance, level of responsibility, potential to assume roles with greater responsibility and experience. The
Compensation Committee reviews salaries on an annual basis and considers merit increases, which are generally effective April&nbsp;1, for all executive officers. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Annual Cash Incentive Program </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design the Annual Cash Incentive Program to
motivate our NEOs to help us reach our annual financial and strategic goals and to reward them for their contributions toward achieving those goals. The Compensation Committee sets each NEO&#146;s target and maximum annual incentive opportunity at
the beginning of the year. The amount that the Compensation Committee actually awards to a NEO is based on the financial results achieved during the year and the NEO&#146;s contribution to those results. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;43 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Annual Cash Incentive Program Award Formula </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2013, the Compensation Committee used this formula to determine awards made under the Annual Cash Incentive Program. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g613688g77w29.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Base salary is discussed above. Below is a discussion of the balance of the elements in this formula. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="80%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#4c4c4c" STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Award Formula Element</FONT></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt;border-bottom:1.00pt solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff">Key Provisions</FONT></B></FONT></P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Target Annual Incentive</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Opportunity</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">2013 target percentage of base salary reflects each
NEO&#146;s role and responsibilities.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CEO: 150%</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CFO: 90%</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;All Other NEOs: 80%</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="font-size:1px; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:6pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">&nbsp;</TD></TR>

<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="80%"></TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee chose these performance measures because they wanted to incent
executives to increase:</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;top line growth;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;bottom line growth; and</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;positive cash flow.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">In establishing the Annual Cash Incentive Program&#146;s 2013 business unit performance measures, the
Compensation Committee determined that if a business unit met its targets, it would receive a business unit rating of 100% and that business unit performance that exceeded or failed to meet target would result in correlating positive or negative
adjustments.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">The Compensation Committee weighted the business unit ratings under the Annual Cash Incentive Program for Messrs. Cofer and Clouse for 2013
as follows: 30% of the business unit rating would be based on their respective business unit&#146;s rating and 70% would be based on the Company&#146;s rating. The Compensation Committee structured their performance standards both to promote
&#147;line-of-sight&#148; accountability and to reinforce the importance of collaboration across the enterprise. Business unit ratings for our other NEOs were aligned 100% to the Company&#146;s rating.</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="font-size:1px; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:6pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">U.S. dollars in millions </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Business Unit Ratings for our European and North American Operations Considered in
Determining the 2013 Program Awards for Mr.&nbsp;Cofer and Mr. Clouse </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In September 2013, Mr.&nbsp;Cofer transitioned from leading our European region to leading
our Asia Pacific and Eastern Europe, Middle East&nbsp;and Africa regions. Because of the timing of his move, Mr.&nbsp;Cofer&#146;s annual cash incentive was based on our European business unit rating. The Compensation Committee considered the
following targets, actual results and overall business unit ratings in Europe and North America in determining the 2013 awards for Mr.&nbsp;Cofer and Mr.&nbsp;Clouse, respectively, under the Annual Cash Incentive Program: </P>

quantifiable&#151;such as how well we performed based on innovation, portfolio management, talent management and the quality of our results. For 2013, the Compensation Committee did not exercise this discretion. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Non-GAAP Financial Measures </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">While we report our financial results in accordance with U.S. GAAP, we based our incentive programs&#146; financial targets, including the Annual Cash Incentive Program,
on non-GAAP financial measures. The chart below describes adjustments to the related GAAP measure and our reasons for using these measures. (See Exhibit A and our Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2013 for additional
information on our Non-GAAP Financial Measures and definitions of terms used below.) </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Measure</FONT></B></FONT></P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Defined Free Cash Flow<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">Free Cash Flow (Net Cash Provided By Operating Activities less capital
expenditures) excluding:</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;net cash received due to the resolution of the Starbucks
arbitration,</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;the cash payments made for accrued interest and other
related fees associated with the debt tendered on December 18, 2013, and</P> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;cash payments (net of tax benefits) associated with
Spin-Off Costs and 2012-2014 Restructuring Program expenditures.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:8pt">Reflects Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s financial liquidity, working capital efficiency and financial health</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Segment Operating Income is a measure of operating income by segment and excludes unrealized gains and losses on hedging activities (which are a component of cost of sales), general corporate expenses (which are a
component of selling, general and administrative expenses), amortization of intangibles, the benefit from the Cadbury acquisition-related indemnification resolution (which is a component of selling, general and administrative expenses), gains and
losses from divestitures and acquisitions and acquisition-related costs (which are a component of selling, general and administrative expenses) for all periods presented. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;46 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Long-Term Incentives </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design
long-term incentive equity grants to align the interests of our executive officers with those of our shareholders. For 2013, the Compensation Committee determined that the appropriate mix of grants in our long-term incentive program for senior
management, including our NEOs, was 50% performance shares, 25% NQSOs and 25% restricted stock, the same mix used since 2008. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g613688g95a66.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Equity Grants &#150; Non-Qualified Stock Options and Restricted Stock </I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee has annually granted NQSOs and restricted stock as a way to align executive compensation with the interests of our shareholders. In 2013, the
Compensation Committee made grants to our NEOs where half the grant value was delivered in restricted stock and half delivered in NQSOs based on its view that this equity mix balances the retention value of restricted stock with the performance
related value of NQSOs. To maintain this balance, based on Black-Scholes valuation, the Compensation Committee adjusted the ratio of restricted stock grants to NQSO grants from one to six in 2012 to one to five in 2013. To help retain valued
executives, restricted stock grants do not vest until the third anniversary of the grant date. The NQSOs vest 33%&nbsp;per year for the first two years on the anniversary date of the grant with the remaining 34% vesting on the third anniversary of
the grant date. U.S. employees on international assignment, such as Mr.&nbsp;Cofer, receive grants of deferred stock units instead of restricted stock, which have the same three-year vesting schedule as restricted stock. Dividends are paid on
unvested restricted stock, and dividend equivalents are paid on deferred stock units at the same time and rate as dividends are paid on Mondel&#275;z International common stock. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee bases grant ranges on an analysis of competitive market practice, with the midpoint of the equity grant ranges, inclusive of the value of the
target performance shares (see &#147;&#150; Grants of Performance Share Units under our Long-Term Incentive Plan&#148; discussion below), approximately equal to the total long-term incentive median of the Compensation Survey Group. It may make an
equity grant above or below the midpoint based on its qualitative review of the executive officer&#146;s individual performance and its evaluation of the executive officer&#146;s potential to assume roles with greater responsibility. Generally,
grants are between 50% and 150% of the midpoint. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;47 </FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All equity grants made to our NEOs in 2013 fell within the respective ranges presented above. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Actual equity grants made are presented in this Proxy Statement in the 2013 Grants of Plan-Based Awards Table under &#147;Executive Compensation Tables.&#148; </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The date that restricted stock and NQSOs grants are made annually is pre-determined based on the scheduled date of the Compensation Committee meeting following the
release of our annual financial results. The grant price for NQSOs is determined on the date the Compensation Committee approves the grants and is the average of the high and low trading prices on that date. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>2012 Special CEO Equity Grant </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In December 2012, the Compensation Committee
made Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld a special equity grant valued at approximately $10,000,000. The grant consisted of: 1) restricted stock (20% of grant) and 2) performance-contingent restricted stock units (80% of grant). The award of shares relating to the
performance-contingent restricted stock units hinges on Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld satisfying specified retention requirements and the Mondel&#275;z International share price exceeding specific price thresholds for a minimum of 10 consecutive trading days:
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt">25.0%</TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During 2013, the first two share price thresholds were met. Even though two of the share price thresholds have been met,
Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld will not receive any award of Company shares in connection with this performance contingent grant prior to December&nbsp;19, 2015. She would also completely forfeit any award if she leaves the Company prior to December&nbsp;19,
2014, except in the case of death, disability or a change in control if Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld is not retained as CEO or the Company shares are not convertible into the acquiring entity&#146;s shares. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Grants of Performance Share Units under our Long-Term Incentive Plan </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Compensation Committee designed the LTIP to motivate executive officers to achieve long-term financial goals and deliver top-tier shareholder returns. The Compensation Committee sets performance targets for a three-year period relating to a grant.
The grants made in 2013 are for the three-year period ending December&nbsp;31, 2015. At the end of the three-year period, the Compensation Committee will only award Company shares if results meet or exceed performance thresholds it sets at the
beginning of the cycle. The number of shares awarded to an executive officer will depend on the achievement of key internal financial measures and TSR relative to the median of our Performance Peer Group. No individual performance factor is used in
the calculation, and no dividends or dividend </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;48 </FONT></P>

award dividend equivalents on shares earned for the performance cycle. Any dividend equivalents will accrue during the performance period and be paid out in cash as of the award date for the performance cycle&#151;which generally occurs in the first
quarter following the end of the performance cycle, provided the Compensation Committee awards shares. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee uses the following formula to
